arfdKC02TFLdxZ7KD2VfjEIYXU8VV8SwovKAnZbihzQ5W2r6mOPtu_omNs6gcjJZV7nxSQ8tO1GYrj5hjmeXtqO-duRk6zdmpF1jYMpfvbcV35Ape6vyH22C6j7lrFtnrskXHxh6F-ZF18iXJO_mEZ_fnoPrnzplL1J5dBaLCSoZCEme877KVE0731ke4WIJwerifi1myzahqstist3QrCvwAvp4yv0n1e7fQlIo_5Joqcmn8QX-LmoYO0eIDMlKHR_dnaC5Jn6CRAbhbOLI7J1o8jrS0KkznJbEch3b4baKw==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating sorting issues**\\n\\nI need to look into the fastutil documentation, particularly regarding `quickSort(int[] x, int[] y)`, which sorts two arrays lexicographically. I wonder if it's sorting them indirectly instead. I do know the primitive arrays have `quickSort(x, y)` for pairs.\\n\\nAnother concern is with `IntBigArrays.wrap(new int[]{...})`, which returns a big array. If the array length is zero, it might involve different handling. Also, `IntIterators.unwrap(concatenated)` seems to have a limit with `Integer.MAX_VALUE`, possibly returning unexpected values.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented comprehensive fastutil 8.1.1 integration tests in:\n\n`tests/src/it.unimi.dsi/fastutil/8.1.1/src/test/java/it_unimi_dsi/fastutil/FastutilTest.java`\n\nCoverage added for:\n- Primitive lists, iterators, sublists, and bulk element operations\n- Primitive/object hash maps, default return values, remapping APIs, cloning, entry sets\n- Primitive sorted sets and bidirectional iteration\n- Linked open hash maps with access-order movement\n- Primitive priority queues with natural and custom comparators\n- Primitive array and big-array utilities\n- Iterator adapters and unmodifiable wrappers\n- `BinIO` primitive array/file/data-stream round trips\n\nNo build files were modified. Per instruction, I did not compile or run the tests.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_016bf80fa9d950870169f938998438819f86f9b7553f0071a1\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4434, "output": 908, "cacheRead": 35328, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40670, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777940623341, "responseId": "resp_016bf80fa9d950870169f9388fce64819f8a7c610ffbe4b50b"}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Investigating sorting issues**\n\nI need to look into the fastutil documentation, particularly regarding `quickSort(int[] x, int[] y)`, which sorts two arrays lexicographically. I wonder if it's sorting them indirectly instead. I do know the primitive arrays have `quickSort(x, y)` for pairs.\n\nAnother concern is with `IntBigArrays.wrap(new int[]{...})`, which returns a big array. If the array length is zero, it might involve different handling. Also, `IntIterators.unwrap(concatenated)` seems to have a limit with `Integer.MAX_VALUE`, possibly returning unexpected values.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_016bf80fa9d950870169f9389090e0819fb8baa05a8c08d2c7\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-TiZSWmBSujYFxIjJUOX-Iw5XEBN5Gx1C1oJo-fXwiosXpJjB-psPLkAPRqDmCjN9j8YCGu3B-4qH7cOjcpR_aY9i75AW1ZTLPYlSsFgeFRVS10V3iv63pi8t84ev6EhCdux_YBF7etZU-SzYFzEkIr4UPR-D2VjyMSVGWVhzYttWof3fsau8n0D5U_XZPwCQj9yZXwKn2evmkG3huPn2Q9XlSDeD0wLODYYC1YuD6ofEuFtqJefc6xfJp_S2SgEZR7OBsKCwKOvsUNL1L_7bqeXzhEU2UtW823WH17RKrMF4o_iWGSWFz1JAg3XF_fblQ2KwhHAmyh59gz9Ma5XggmR_zq03LBNLnaXpONRPHg0v2Ig_MAg0_l1Hm9T4iBskyJjX7EnjRf16t0GeutQPlecSqLvoGbOnpCDCCQrz3jxkPsB_F5TnJimWk4K-Q8nqGaLikfWjAqqIdo_yPS-B1Crmwc2hOgCTuJOYyhAL9UCQONu-cPAPZtb99cY1RuOFSDEdp1tMouUF5fSb943oXj0n1kNXmTdz5bIJTHAH3SRkJKf2-KLTgOWkoM2Zlb5EkvRUWmdu6-WVJ5Z08Zz5eSNcXtnYNfg38O9Ea8Gl0jWmaUPsKzobHD7IzzsByhQLIOkm-i0Lrqh9XHYhwQkbuAhXG7kjYfLMpDjE23jMjKnnMDVQsJavo1yijx0nDzA0DXFB9odBX3QbeUmTLiN1l-gn-_J8dKnhD6WMqUDNPCU-uIpL4tRrelMA1R4GMnASm2c9zJOa8IHodnf7Pn-u06FtZiY4NzE5VJS1hkYea5R088bOu4DwwI2aAyWy1owyDGcG8R7zpjpTGSBrykJSWUqPFtwn5Gg6SuuVxDb1p-NnVbbXe-l9afSkaS2FrY0XrYn1aG-B-lRkXD3vnZ5zYrb-OSolZ-y_1OVp7toa6uEyMvAKYUEELv7ynthtJQcJIC8DjePTHRt5oX14mCuK-tbbdQKrwFcXSZ_DJD-8nnPl_Yt01a9zwIhisQ8JFTzT10ZTsIZWWDRXxiCWe6sOcP9Zo5CQBLe1sislW2DUVlDhATzPXYmi3bCw-P73CLGLfUfLcWGfBVk7BSk2ccbRZ-hKIoh0Who7VHfpYqaHQmfLMIjYdTEFEkNUdywXisoohX9Kaybqd8YTVct