dKC02TFLdxZ7KD2VfjEIYXU8VV8SwovKAnZbihzQ5W2r6mOPtu_omNs6gcjJZV7nxSQ8tO1GYrj5hjmeXtqO-duRk6zdmpF1jYMpfvbcV35Ape6vyH22C6j7lrFtnrskXHxh6F-ZF18iXJO_mEZ_fnoPrnzplL1J5dBaLCSoZCEme877KVE0731ke4WIJwerifi1myzahqstist3QrCvwAvp4yv0n1e7fQlIo_5Joqcmn8QX-LmoYO0eIDMlKHR_dnaC5Jn6CRAbhbOLI7J1o8jrS0KkznJbEch3b4baKw==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating sorting issues**\\n\\nI need to look into the fastutil documentation, particularly regarding `quickSort(int[] x, int[] y)`, which sorts two arrays lexicographically. I wonder if it's sorting them indirectly instead. I do know the primitive arrays have `quickSort(x, y)` for pairs.\\n\\nAnother concern is with `IntBigArrays.wrap(new int[]{...})`, which returns a big array. If the array length is zero, it might involve different handling. Also, `IntIterators.unwrap(concatenated)` seems to have a limit with `Integer.MAX_VALUE`, possibly returning unexpected values.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented comprehensive fastutil 8.1.1 integration tests in:\n\n`tests/src/it.unimi.dsi/fastutil/8.1.1/src/test/java/it_unimi_dsi/fastutil/FastutilTest.java`\n\nCoverage added for:\n- Primitive lists, iterators, sublists, and bulk element operations\n- Primitive/object hash maps, default return values, remapping APIs, cloning, entry sets\n- Primitive sorted sets and bidirectional iteration\n- Linked open hash maps with access-order movement\n- Primitive priority queues with natural and custom comparators\n- Primitive array and big-array utilities\n- Iterator adapters and unmodifiable wrappers\n- `BinIO` primitive array/file/data-stream round trips\n\nNo build files were modified. Per instruction, I did not compile or run the tests.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_016bf80fa9d950870169f938998438819f86f9b7553f0071a1\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4434, "output": 908, "cacheRead": 35328, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens":